The forces of the mega strike are gathering
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will form, on Friday, their strike commission that will be responsible for coordinating Monday's indefinite strike.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the Health Insurance Act, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic jams because rail traffic will be stopped almost completely and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 13h.
The unions of the league will make known, Friday afternoon, the details of their strike on Monday, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike committee of LIGA - MOSZ will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of Monday's actions.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held, and as of Monday, organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health insurance, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not pass the Health Funds Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strikes.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide what action to take.
According to the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the Health Funds Act will take place only late at night, or even at night.
Due to the planned strike on Monday, major traffic jams are planned: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Vol<0xC3><0xA1>n companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call for strikes, the list of which is constantly updated on the League's website.
Some organizations report going on strike for an indefinite period, others have declared a temporary work stoppage.
Until Thursday afternoon, the M<0xC3><0x81>V (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, and as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the start of service until 1 pm, the airport in Budapest between 7 am and 9 am, the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Teachers' Union have called for strikes for 2 hours and from 2 to 8 hours respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country alternately, the Health and Social Sector Employees Union (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will strike a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, made by the League, requires the government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new conception to the social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be implemented from next year be introduced in several steps.
The third claim calls for a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, which would allow the system to transfer the functions that deserve it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport regarding secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard Increased Country Risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarorsz<0xC3><0xA1>gért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several aspects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “risk warning”, the company points out that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes may occur following the worsening of the already existing ethnic tension between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely aimed at provoking this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: “public actors passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings who based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians.”
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially regarding confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of Hungarian radical and far-right groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 giving themselves the name of "national self-defense association".
“The common feature of these rallies is that they define themselves as a civilian organization while publicly declaring the preparation of their members for defense missions (catastrophes, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, in addition, referring to the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words the state,” they added.
They pointed out that everything was going according to the method that, based on the grudge of the political society and the parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions from a civil aspect.
The emphasis on civility and association status therefore serves only to avoid the legal pitfalls of registering these associations in court, but they also constitute a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a factor that also increases the risk compared to neighboring relations.
“In recent months, many neighbouring countries have cited the Hungarian Guard as a potential source of risk and ultra-nationalist political actors in some neighbouring countries want to justify their anti-Hungarian policy by referring to the Hungarian Guard’s constitution.
This influences the political stability of the region,” they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not a unique phenomenon in Eastern Central Europe, political risks have increased across the region.
As they say, the functioning of the Hungarian Guard resembles, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard whose constitution was declared by the Bulgarian National Union (BNU) in August 2007.
The numerous Roma unrest that erupted in a district of Sofia (Kraszna Poljana) is at the origin of the constitution of the Bulgarian guard.
Taking advantage of these events, the UNB decided to form a guard, saying that the organization's objective is "national self-defense".
According to them, in the last 17 years, the Gypsies have “terrorized” Bulgaria but the state has remained inactive and neutral, recalls the Political Capital.
They added that the initiative had sparked lively debates in Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the statement by some Bulgarian Roma organizations regarding the formation of their own guard as a form of resistance signals the increased risk of ethnic clashes.
The operation of the Hungarian Guard showing similarities to that of the Bulgarian National Guard does not exclude that the Hungarian Roma react to the threat in the same way by organizing their own self-defense, the Political Capital risk warning reads.
Attila Juh<0xC3><0xA1>sz, director of research at Political Capital, said: Risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, their risk analysis is published every year and if events occur that could have an impact on the change in risk, they inform the public, as in this case, by issuing a risk warning.
The party is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holidays and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
The holidays are not uniform in the EU and the US either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national and state holidays as well as rest days.
Days of rest are often linked to religious holidays or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the New Year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, the latter all the more so that the holidaymakers can rest quietly.
In addition, in a year, we have a total of eleven parties marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as is October 23, which is also the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1st is Labor Day and November 1st and 2nd, we remember our deceased family members and friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, depending on the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases where there is only one working day left before or after the holiday marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price for extended weekends by working or going to school on the Saturday before the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in a special regulation on the replacement days of the days before or after the holidays.
The law extends to all employers and all their employees, to civil servants and to persons working in the public service.
It does not, however, apply to service companies, institutions operating without interruption and in service, by their vocation, and also for days of rest.
This year, working days will be changed only around the end of the year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost all over the country because according to experiences the majority of people rather do overtime or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes to be able to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
Next year many holidays fall in the middle or at the end of the week, therefore there will be fewer changes in the level of working days compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized for the first time around Labor Day to allow employees to stay at home for four days in a row.
Saturday, April 25th will be a working day to have a day off on Friday, May 2nd.
Another change is planned for October 23: Saturday, October 18 will be a working day replacing Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if the day of the new year falls on a Wednesday.
Six futile things that can bother colleagues terribly
Emails that we forget to send, voice messages that we never receive, innocent lies that annoy us almost no more: these are things that “beautify” the daily life of a workplace.
The question is whether one gets used to these problems or meets the challenge and consciously avoids ambiguous situations, causing trouble to others.
Examples.
“Excuse me, I forgot to tell you that you were called from the marketing department,” a colleague told you.
That you missed a date?
At best he is sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to pass on the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, this is arranged with an apology.
Before having painful explanations, it is helpful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
Are you borrowing something that doesn't belong to you?
There’s nothing more annoying than wanting to pick up a file, an office tool or the phone and you can’t find them anywhere.
Remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Don't take anything from your colleagues without asking or they're right to be angry at you for stealing their property.
Don’t bring any envelopes or post-its back in your pocket because it can be annoying that there aren’t any more and you need them right away.
Are you talking about co-workers' privacy?
There are no good ways to stop gossip from spreading.
Who did what, with whom?
Or and why?
Don’t tell everyone your information (assumptions) about your colleagues’ privacy!
If a colleague shares his or her intimate secrets with you, don’t misuse his or her trust!
Bury the information shared within yourself and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware of it.
Are you professing to be ill for no good reason?
When you call the office and declare yourself sick under the pretext of a heartbreaking headache because you feel sick or feel you need rest that day, think about the fact that your work, your urgent affairs, your missions in the future must be carried out by someone else in your place.
Don't bother your colleagues!
If you know in advance that the next day you will not go to work or that something may happen that would force you to stay at home, do not forget to inform your boss and your colleagues so that they will not be surprised by your absence the next day.
Chilling, grinning, phone
Are you immersed in your work but the laughing of your colleagues takes you out of it brutally?
Have you unwittingly become a witness to a phone conversation you'd better not listen to?
Don’t bother your colleagues with humming, chanting, chattering aloud (which you lead over their head), kicking, big words or discontent expressed aloud.
They can disturb even if your colleagues are not immersed in a project (writing, design, organization).
Are you accusing others of a mistake?
If your work is not done for the deadline, you forget to send a letter or an important message, do not accuse anyone for this forgetting!
Don’t put it on account of the eventual chaos in the office or your noisy colleagues!
Recognize it if you made a mistake and if it presented inconvenience to others, repair the fault!
Ask how you can repair your fault, repair the negligence!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Wearing jogging and slippers is comfortable at home but they are not suitable for the office!
Do not wear comfortable jogging even if your function allows it!
Do not be neglected, respect your colleagues and yourself by dressing properly, and if your function requires it by putting on pretty and elegant clothes, to go to work!
