Cuba still offers a fantasy that is unique in the world and that will be appreciated especially by lovers of small trains.
The cane had re-entered from the plantations extended into the sweet shops on a narrow track by small steam and motor trains.
Their rolling stock has not been renewed for decades and this is how we can see small locomotives running, whose contemporaries are not only in museums elsewhere.
Where to direct his steps?
The majority of visitors do not miss the most well-known places.
There is no need to write much about Varadero or Havana.
Otherwise remember that in the Hemingway property, already mentioned, there is a museum and whoever loves this writer should not miss the visit.
The Vi<0xC5><0x88>ales Valley in the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
Exuberant vegetation grows there on limestone soil.
Mogotes, limestone balloons and rocks rise from the bottom of the valley, and, as fertile soil has become trapped in their bowels, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetal carpet.
The valley is probably the place where Cuban tobacco of the best quality is grown.
You will be able to meet the final shape of this product if you visit one of the cigar factories in Havana.
Perhaps someone will also find it interesting that this is where the Chilean episode of Major Zeman was shot.
Trinidad
An ancient town founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
It was the slave trade and the sugar trade that brought him glory and wealth.
