Koloni<0xC3><0xA1>ln<0xC3><0xAD> <0xC5><0xA1>pan<0xC4><0x9B>lsk<0xC3><0xA1> architektura,v<0xC3><0xBD>razn<0xC4><0x9B> ovlivn<0xC4><0x9B>n<0xC3><0xA1> pozd<0xC4><0x9B>j<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD>mi francouzsk<0xC3><0xBD>mi osadn<0xC3><0xAD>ky, if <0xC4><0x8D>ty<0xC5><0x99>i stalet<0xC3><0xAD> tem<0xC4><0x9B><0xC5><0x99> nezm<0xC4><0x9B>nila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain massif, is a place so remote that even in the 50's of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay on his side.
We didn't build anything, and that's why we didn't demolish anything either, everyone just had a roof over their heads.
If you have more time in Trinidad than an afternoon, then it is also worth going to see interesting places in the surroundings, such as Playa Anc<0xC3><0xB3>n beach or the Sugar Valley.
