This opinion is certainly already influenced by the path that leads to it.
The two roads leading from Guant<0xC3><0xA1>namo must cross high and rugged mountains and cross a landscape almost without marks of human activity.
UNESCO has inscribed the eastern reef of Cuba, thanks to its intact landscape, on the World Heritage List.
The best chocolate is made in the church, there is the Christopher Columbus Cross (in reality, it was born about a hundred years after Columbus' journey) and from the hill where the old castle and the current El Castillo hotel are located, you can see several table mountains, the most famous of which is El Yunque.
About coffee, rum, cigars, the Sierra Maestra mountain range, the Bay of Sows and Isla de Pinos Island, the Tropicana Cabaret, the sanctuary of the patron saint of Cuba Caridad del Cobre, the Santeria, the African religions practiced by the descendants of the ancient slaves, about all this we could fill a lot.
