Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force on November 1
Alongside its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members of Parliament and Senators to negotiate and consent to the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activity of agencies so that markets function effectively.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the different leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services for both specialized corporate purposes and to individuals or legal entities and creates a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial advisory firms (AFIs), which merge with securities firms, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that it is possible to add multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems to regulated secondary markets, which compete with current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose to the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
Through the Congressional Economics Commission, several changes have been added, including one that highlights that securitized debt will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of high-risk U.S. mortgages (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of the management took advantage to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after in 1977, was approved, the Royal Decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting new clients to different investment companies at the same time.
