Schäuble warns against riots like those in France.
Street fights with police, gunfire, cars on fire: Wolfgang Schäuble warns against riots like those in France.
Everything must be done to ensure that social dissatisfaction in Germany does not erupt in the streets with violence, the German Interior Minister demanded.
Burning barricades, busters firing at the police with shotguns: after the serious youth riots in France, German Interior Minister Wolfgang Schäuble (CDU) fears similar developments in Germany.
We must ensure that a social explosive does not also form in our country and defuses itself in violence.
We must take this seriously," he told the "New Press" in Hanover.
Not all young individuals would be able to cope with the rapid transformations of social reality.
The Federation, the federated states and the communes were already working hard to reduce the problems, Schäuble said.
This would not only affect the integration of immigrants.
“From integration summits to conferences on Islam, it already shows its first successes.”
But it would be too early for an end to the alarm.
Schäuble points out at the same time that in the German suburbs, there are no sociological problems nor from the point of view of urbanism as in France.
